<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Not JUST that. Let's FLAME -PvP a sec too</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?doodzillamastakillamofo of Doom">doodzillamastakillamofo of Doom</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:45 p.m. 26/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Not JUST that. Let's FLAME -PvP a sec too<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1126" TARGET=_self>Not JUST that. Let's FLAME -PvP a sec too</A> (Gray Rage (DB))
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>&gt; The bottom line is that the +PvP server is, in all actuality, a
<BR>&gt; BETTER role play server than ANY of the others! The other
<BR>&gt; servers simply exist as a place where folks go because they are
<BR>&gt; simply afraid of direct agressive confrontation with other
<BR>&gt; players. They conveniently use the crutch of 'role play' to hide
<BR>&gt; their fears and cowardice.
<P>From the previous posts griping of equipment stealing and so forth, as well as the considerable time spent to get ANYWHERE in EQ, I believe a lot of people simply don't have the time to deal with the aggravation of the PVP server. I personally can't play 12+ hours a day, and if I did, I am sure that my work would fire me! ;)
<P>What I am disagreeing with is your statement regarding people using the crutch of roleplay to hide their fears and cowardice. I personally like the game as is (non-PVP) just for a few simple reasons:
<BR>I can get up and use the john without worrying that some 12 yr old with an 8 foot troll smashes my character to bits while I'm sitting down BECAUSE HE CAN.
<BR>And as much fun as PVP is, you meet the biggest losers whose sole entire purpose is to make your gaming experience a living hell. They will always exist, and will exist in final. It is human nature.
<BR>It is a lot of fun to party with friends and kill the monsters...especially with things like battlefield communicator.
<BR>If I want massive death and killing I will go play Starsiege Tribes.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
